│ from LHS into `Pred`, but `m_SpecificCmp(Pred, ...)` then tries to match    │
│ RHS with that same predicate. The problem is that `CmpInst::Predicate`      │
│ includes both the comparison type (e.g., ICMP_UGT) AND the samesign flag as │
│ part of the predicate value. When LHS has predicate 'samesign ugt' and RHS  │
│ has predicate 'sgt', they are different predicates, but the matching logic  │
│ incorrectly allows this transformation because it doesn't properly account  │
│ for the fact that these are fundamentally different comparison operations.  │
│                                                                             │
│ Looking at the debugger output, we can see that LHS is 'icmp samesign ugt'  │
│ while RHS is 'icmp sgt', yet the code proceeds with the transformation. The │
│ `IsCommutative` check also fails because icmp_ugt is not commutative.       │
│                                                                             │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s): The issue is in the pattern matching logic at    │
│ lines 1680-1684. We need to ensure that when matching comparison            │
│ operations, we properly verify that both comparisons are truly equivalent,  │
│ including their samesign attributes. The current code uses                  │
│ `m_SpecificCmp(Pred, ...)` which should enforce exact predicate matching,   │
│ but there appears to be an issue with how the predicate is being handled.   │
│                                                                             │
