has predicate 'samesign ugt' and RHS has predicate 'sgt', they are different
predicates, but the matching logic incorrectly allows this transformation
because it doesn't properly account for the fact that these are fundamentally
different comparison operations.\n\nLooking at the debugger output, we can see
that LHS is 'icmp samesign ugt' while RHS is 'icmp sgt', yet the code proceeds
with the transformation. The `IsCommutative` check also fails because icmp_ugt
is not commutative.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s): The issue is in the pattern
matching logic at lines 1680-1684. We need to ensure that when matching
comparison operations, we properly verify that both comparisons are truly
equivalent, including their samesign attributes. The current code uses
`m_SpecificCmp(Pred, ...)` which should enforce exact predicate matching, but
there appears to be an issue with how the predicate is being
handled.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the code, the real issue is
